Lagos State Deputy Governor, Dr. Obafemi Hamzat, yesterday seized two buses and a Corolla car for driving against traffic on the Lagos-Badagry Expressway and Ikorodu Road respectively. The first commercial bus driver was arrested at Agboju area of Lagos-Badagry Expressway for driving against the traffic, while the other driver was also accosted driving on BRT lane at Ojota area of Ikorodu Road. Also, a Corolla carâ€™s owner was arrested by the team of policemen on the entourage of the deputy governor for driving against traffic between Alaka and Costain Bus Stop on Funsho Williams Road. The deputy governor ordered that the vehicles be impounded according to executive order issued by Governor Babajide Sanwo-Olu recently on indiscriminate driving against traffic in the metropolis. Speaking at the resumption of construction work on the Lagos-Badagry Expressway, Hamzat urged citizens to obey the state traffic rules. The deputy governor said he had observed that many Lagosians were in the habit of flouting traffic rules.